  section
    .container-fluid
      .row.panel.panel--remitly-intro
        .default-text.text-center.round-xs(style="background:none; padding: 40px")
          h1 The Remitly design system
          h2.visible-lg.visible-xl &nbsp;

      .row
        .default-text.round-bottom-sm
          h2 Context

          p As Remitly scaled its money sending operations from 3 countries to roughly a dozen, managing location-specific implementations became costly. Engineering made the decision to replace the front end with something more maintainable, which was the right opportunity to also overhaul a UI that hadn’t gotten much love in the past

          p The new design system helped us keep a consistent execution across multiple corridors with customized experiences based on cultural and regulatory expectations, while also serving as a platform for quickly testing variations on the product, scaling to accomodate a complex fintech product with <strong>over $7 billion in annual throughput</strong>.

      //- Existing brand widget
      .panel.panel--remitly-pale.round-bottom-sm.round-lg
        .row(style="padding:0 16px")
          .col-sm-20.col-sm-offset-2.col-md-18.col-md-offset-3.shadow(style="background-color:white; padding: 80px 0; overflow: hidden;")
            .col-xs-18.col-xs-offset-3.col-xl-7.col-xl-offset-2.md-vertical-center(style="padding-bottom: 20px;")
              h4(style="color: #FF3F00; margin-bottom: 0;") Context
              h2(style="color: #173A4A; margin-top: 0;") Existing brand
              
              p The first pass at a mobile version of this app adhered closely to 
                a(href="https://web.archive.org/web/20180212064432/http://www.weareairlift.com/case-study/remitly") the existing print guidlines
                | - dark backgrounds, and white text on bright reds and greens. However, it wasn’t long until the glaring UX implications led us to develop an alternate theme that would incorporate form design best practices - especially around error handling, while still feeling on-brand.

            .col-xs-18.col-xs-offset-3.col-xl-11.col-xl-offset-2
              img(src="/img/remitly/remitly_existing_brand_simple.png", style="width: 100%;")

